3 Ajustar modelo

mod <- lmer(Calificacion ~ SOI * Canal * Sexo +
              (1 + SOI | `ID Participante`) +
              (1 | Estimulo),
            data = bd,
            control = lmerControl(optimizer = "bobyqa"))

3.1 EcuaciÃ³n modelo

3.3 Resumen del modelo

pval.lev <- function(pvals) {
  ifelse(pvals < 0.0001,
         "<b>< 0.0001</b>",
         ifelse(pvals < 0.001,
                "<b>< 0.001</b>",
                ifelse(pvals < 0.05,
                       paste0("<b>", round(pvals, 4), "</b>"),
                       round(pvals, 2))))
}

3.4 Reporte en texto

rep.mod <- report(mod, format = "markdown")

We fitted a linear mixed model (estimated using REML and BOBYQA optimizer) to predict Calificacion with SOI (formula: Calificacion ~ SOI * Canal * Sexo). The model included SOI as random effects (formula: list(~1 + SOI | ID Participante, ~1 | Estimulo)). The modelâs total explanatory power is substantial (conditional R2 = 0.28) and the part related to the fixed effects alone (marginal R2) is of 0.02. The modelâs intercept, corresponding to SOI = 0, is at 4.95 (95% CI [4.45, 5.46], t(12157) = 19.27, p < .001). Within this model:

  • The effect of SOI is statistically significant and negative (beta = -0.16, 95% CI [-0.29, -0.02], t(12157) = -2.27, p = 0.023; Std. beta = -0.11, 95% CI [-0.20, -0.01])
  • The effect of Canal [Voz] is statistically significant and positive (beta = 0.28, 95% CI [6.99e-03, 0.55], t(12157) = 2.01, p = 0.044; Std. beta = 0.31, 95% CI [0.25, 0.37])
  • The effect of Canal [Voz + rostro] is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 0.24, 95% CI [-0.03, 0.51], t(12157) = 1.74, p = 0.082; Std. beta = 0.24, 95% CI [0.18, 0.30])
  • The effect of Sexo [Mujer] is statistically significant and negative (beta = -1.07, 95% CI [-1.87, -0.26], t(12157) = -2.59, p = 0.010; Std. beta = -0.03, 95% CI [-0.23, 0.18])
  • The interaction effect of Canal [Voz] on SOI is statistically significant and positive (beta = 0.15, 95% CI [0.06, 0.23], t(12157) = 3.33, p < .001; Std. beta = 0.10, 95% CI [0.04, 0.16])
  • The interaction effect of Canal [Voz + rostro] on SOI is statistically significant and positive (beta = 0.11, 95% CI [0.02, 0.19], t(12157) = 2.46, p = 0.014; Std. beta = 0.07, 95% CI [0.01, 0.13])
  • The interaction effect of Sexo [Mujer] on SOI is statistically significant and positive (beta = 0.29, 95% CI [0.10, 0.48], t(12157) = 3.06, p = 0.002; Std. beta = 0.20, 95% CI [0.07, 0.33])
  • The interaction effect of Sexo [Mujer] on Canal [Voz] is statistically significant and positive (beta = 0.83, 95% CI [0.38, 1.28], t(12157) = 3.60, p < .001; Std. beta = -0.05, 95% CI [-0.13, 0.03])
  • The interaction effect of Sexo [Mujer] on Canal [Voz + rostro] is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 0.45, 95% CI [-3.18e-03, 0.90], t(12157) = 1.95, p = 0.052; Std. beta = -0.08, 95% CI [-0.16, -1.61e-03])
  • The interaction effect of Sexo [Mujer] on (SOI * Canal [Voz]) is statistically significant and negative (beta = -0.28, 95% CI [-0.40, -0.16], t(12157) = -4.63, p < .001; Std. beta = -0.19, 95% CI [-0.27, -0.11])
  • The interaction effect of Sexo [Mujer] on (SOI * Canal [Voz + rostro]) is statistically significant and negative (beta = -0.19, 95% CI [-0.31, -0.07], t(12157) = -3.15, p = 0.002; Std. beta = -0.13, 95% CI [-0.21, -0.05])

Standardized parameters were obtained by fitting the model on a standardized version of the dataset. 95% Confidence Intervals (CIs) and p-values were computed using a Wald t-distribution approximation., We fitted a linear mixed model (estimated using REML and BOBYQA optimizer) to predict Calificacion with Canal (formula: Calificacion ~ SOI * Canal * Sexo). 3.5 Explorar interacciÃ³n Canal:SOI:Sexo

Calcular correlaciÃ³n entre sociosexualidad auto-reportada y estimada por canal y sexo

slopes <- sim_slopes(mod,
                     pred = SOI,
                     modx = Canal,
                     mod2 = Sexo)

slopes.fin <- rbind(data.frame(slopes$slopes[1]),
             data.frame(slopes$slopes[2])) |>
  select(1,2,4,5,7) |>
  mutate(across(2:5, as.numeric)) |>
  mutate(across(2:5, round, 3)) |>
  mutate(Sexo = rep(c("Hombre", "Mujer"), each = 3)) |>
  select(6,1:5) |>
  rename(Canal = Value.of.Canal) |>
  rename(r = Est.)

slopes.audio <- filter(slopes.fin, Canal == "Voz")
slopes.audiovisual <- filter(slopes.fin, Canal == "Voz + rostro")
slopes.foto <- filter(slopes.fin, Canal == "Rostro")
